Reasoning: This paper focuses on understanding the socio-technical attributes of developers in open source software projects and how they relate to being mentioned in GitHub discussions. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper uses statistical models to analyze the data, which could also fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SD), cybernetics (cs.CY), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
